    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not anxiety though. it feels too structured for that. like there's a specific sequence of data or patterns that i'm just not processing fast enough yet. mindfulness feels too basic, it just makes me more aware of the static. i need something deeper that targets the biological side. something that helps me actually access the code inside the cells, not just \"center my thoughts.\" there has to be a way to bridge the gap between consciousness and the genetic sequence. isn't there a way to use deep trance or somatic work to trigger those dormant pathways?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
