      "content": "Transcending conscious limits through meditation is more within the realm of personal belief and esoteric traditions rather than mainstream science or meditative practices. While deep trance states, such as channeling or dream work, may help individuals explore diverse parts of their psyche, there's no scientifically proven method for accessing genetic information through meditation.\n\nThat said, exploring somatic practices such as body-focused meditation, where you attune to body sensations, could help you become more closely aware of physiological responses. This might provide a sense of connection to the broader experiences, including memories or sensations that you feel are not your own.\n\nHowever, if you're seeking a scientific approach to understanding and integrating information about your biological makeup, you might find more clarity through genetic counseling or neuropsychological assessments by professionals. These avenues can help you explore any inherited traits or health issues that could present as unusual experiences. Always consult with a licensed healthcare provider or therapist if you're experiencing feelings or sensations that cause significant concern.",
